Hi Dana,

Thanks for the detailed request. Currently, per the API Documentation, rate limits are enforced per-project token rather than account-wide, so proj_30021's limit isn't actually shared with your other three projects — each already has its own independent 10,000 req/min ceiling on Enterprise tier. If proj_30021 alone is exceeding 10,000 req/min during spikes, that's a per-project limit being hit, not cross-project contention.

I've logged this as a product feature request (internal ref FR-2216) for configurable per-project limits above the standard Enterprise ceiling, since that's a different ask — effectively a burst allowance for a single high-volume project. I don't have a committed timeline for this yet; I'll follow up when it's scoped by Product.

In the meantime, one workaround: batch your event submissions using the batch-import endpoint for non-real-time data on proj_30021 to reduce request count within the existing limit, if applicable to your use case.

Best,
Marcus
Nimbus Analytics Support
